</em>You have a strong thesis statement from the mini-lesson <em>Developing a strong thesis statement</em>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />How should you put it all together to create an effective essay?<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><p><span class=\"ju-normal\" style=\"color:black;font-family:lato,sans-serif;font-size:16px;\">Essay<br />Why Going to the Movies Is Better Than Watching TV</span></p><p><br /><span class=\"marker\">I have ideas and a thesis statement.&nbsp; When you have your ideas solidly in place, it will be easier to write your introduction.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":null},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"4"},"leftText":"<p>You have already created your thesis statement in the mini-lesson <em>Developing a strong thesis statement:</em><br /><br /><span class=\"ju-examples\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:tahoma;\">Going to the movies is better than staying home because there are no distractions or interruptions at the movies; It is a diagram that uses circles to show the ideas you have for each of the body paragraphs.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Writing Web:</span></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img alt=\"A web has a large center circle surrounded by three smaller circles.  Each of the smaller circles is surrounded by three even smaller circles.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p>","headerText":"Using a web to organize your writing"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"6"},"leftText":"<p>To create a web, start by drawing a circle in the middle of a blank page.<br /><br />Write your topic in the circle:<br /><br /><span class=\"ju-examples\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:tahoma;\">Going to the movies is better than watching TV at home.</span><br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img alt=\"An illustration shows a circle with your topic written in the middle.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"7"},"leftText":"<p>Now draw three circles surrounding the large circle in the middle.<br /><br />Each of the surrounding circles represents one reason why you believe going to the movies is better than watching TV.&nbsp; These reasons are taken from your thesis statement.<br /><br />Write one reason in each surrounding circle.&nbsp; You can use simplified wording to represent each reason.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><img alt=\"Part of your writing web.  The large center circle says going to the movies is better than watching TV at home.   The reasons listed in the three smaller circles surrounding the large center circle are no distractions, the audio visual experience is better, and more active.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"8"},"leftText":"<p>Now draw the smallest circles branching off of the reasons.&nbsp; For each reason, draw two to four small circles.&nbsp; These represent the details that will support your ideas.<br /><br />Write the details and examples that support each reason in the smallest circles.<br /><br />Good writers expect to change, or<em> </em><strong>revise</strong><em>, </em>what they write.&nbsp; You will start with these ideas, and as you go through the writing process, you can expect to change some of them.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img alt=\"An illustration of a writing web shows a topic circle surrounded by three reason circles, each of which have three details circles.
